# Code owners — high-risk modules.
#
# These three modules carry the project's highest regression risk
# (session orchestration, the memory pipeline, the server entry points).
# Every PR touching them must ship a 回归报告 (enforced by
# scripts/check_pr_report.py) AND get a maintainer review.
#
# For the review requirement to actually block merge, enable
# "Require review from Code Owners" in the branch protection rule for `main`
# (GitHub → Settings → Branches). CODEOWNERS alone only auto-requests review.
#
# NOTE: replace @wehos below with the correct maintainer handle / team if it
# differs. GitHub silently ignores entries whose owner can't review the repo.

/app/         @wehos
/main_logic/  @wehos
/memory/      @wehos

# NEKO Live plugin. CN-Zephyr has upstream write access and owns review of
# plugin contracts, runtime behavior, Hosted UI, privacy, and distribution.
/plugin/plugins/neko_live/  @CN-Zephyr
